02/05/2011
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The Democratic Reconstruction of Macedonia (DOM) party and the ruling VMRO-DPMNE will join forces again as coalition for the upcoming June 5th parliamentary elections. VMRO-DPMNE leader Nikola Gruevski met with DOM President Liljana Popovska on Sunday (May 1st) to discuss the parties' priorities in the upcoming four-year period. They agreed that the focus should be on the economy, attracting foreign investments, Euro-Atlantic integration, education and science. Gruevski voiced confidence that the For Better Macedonia coalition will win the snap elections. (Makfax, Alsat M, Dnevnik - 01/05/11)
